[2] Minia governorate: not yet peaked

Date: Sun, 15 Apr 2012
Source: AlWafd [Arabic, mach transl, summarised, edited]
http://tinyurl.com/dxacd9y

Foot and mouth disease - a time bomb
------------------------------------
FMD continues to spread in Minia Governorate, causing mounting concern among farmers and livestock keepers.

According to reports received by the Directorate of Veterinary Medicine, the number of deaths has increased to 1250 head of cattle and 1850 animals are being currently treated in various centers of the province. Farmers and livestock keepers are in panic, in fear of the emergence of the disease in livestock, which is their only source of livelihood.

Published atatements about the payment of compensation were regarded by public as "laughable": no donations have been received so far.

[Byline: Ashraf Kamal]

--
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>



[Subscribers may wish to read FAO's mission report "Rapid Assessment Mission Report on Foot-and-Mouth Disease Management in Egypt", 12-16 March 2012, by Dr Chris Bartels, Veterinary Epidemiologist, EuFMD/FAO consultant, and Dr Eoin Ryan, FAO Animal Health Officer FAO/EuFMD. The report is available at http://www.fao.org/docrep/015/an383e/an383e00.pdf.

Though the sequencing of the Egyptian FMDV SAT2 strain (batch WRLFMD/2012/00011, sent to WRLFMD 12 Mar 2012) has long been accomplished, the results are not yet available on the web-site of WRLFMD; see Egypt's page at http://www.wrlfmd.org/fmd_genotyping/africa/egy.htm.- Mod.AS.



A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1zkM.]

